  "local_port": 43468,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What is a suitable solar panel installation provider in San Jose, California CA?",
  "response": "When selecting a solar panel installation provider in San Jose, CA, consider factors such as reputation, certifications, local experience, customer reviews, warranties, financing options, and their ability to handle permits and incentives. Here\u2019s a curated list of reputable providers, each with unique strengths:\n\n### **Top Solar Providers in San Jose, CA**\n1. **SunPower**  \n   - **Strengths**: Known for high-efficiency panels (Maxeon technology) and industry-leading warranties (25-year comprehensive).  \n   - **Certifications**: NABCEP, SEIA member.  \n   - **Ideal For**: Those prioritizing premium technology and long-term reliability.\n\n2. **Tesla Solar (formerly SolarCity)**  \n   - **Strengths**: Integrated solar + Powerwall battery systems, competitive pricing, and sleek designs.  \n   - **Unique Offer**: Seamless energy storage solutions for outages.  \n   - **Consider**: Mixed reviews on customer service; verify recent feedback.\n\n3. **Solar Technologies**  \n   - **Local Expertise**: San Jose-based with deep knowledge of local regulations (e.g., PG&E net metering) and climate.  \n   - **Certifications**: NABCEP, BBB A+ rating.  \n   - **Specialty**: Custom designs and strong focus on customer education.\n\n4. **California Solar Group (Cal Solar)**  \n   - **Experience**: Over a decade in CA, specializing in residential and commercial projects.  \n   - **Sustainability**: Emphasizes eco-friendly practices and Energy Star partnerships.  \n   - **Warranty**: Robust 25-year panel warranties.\n\n5. **Semper Solaris**  \n   - **USP**: Veteran-owned, offers solar + roofing/battery services.  \n   - **Military Discounts**: Active/retired military may qualify for special pricing.  \n   - **Reputation**: Strong BBB accreditation with transparent pricing.\n\n6. **Sunrun**  \n   - **Financing**: Flexible leasing/PPA options (no upfront costs).  \n   - **Scale**: One of the largest U.S. providers, with extensive support networks.  \n   - **Consider**: Mixed local reviews; compare quotes carefully.\n\n7. **REC Solar**  \n   - **Commercial Focus**: Strong track record in commercial installations but also serves residential clients.  \n   - **Partnerships**: Works with PG&E and other utilities for streamlined processes.\n\n### **Key Considerations**\n- **Licensing**: Verify CSLB licenses and check for pending complaints.  \n- **Local Reviews**: Prioritize companies with recent positive feedback on Yelp/Google and minimal BBB complaints.  \n- **Quotes**: Use platforms like EnergySage to compare 3\u20135 quotes for cost/benefit analysis.  \n- **Incentives**: Ensure providers assist with federal tax credits (26%), CA Net Metering, and local rebates (e.g., Bay Area SunShares).  \n\n### **Final Tips**\n- **Site Assessment**: Opt for free consultations to evaluate your home\u2019s solar potential.  \n- **Weather Adaptation**: San Jose\u2019s fog and heat require durable panels; discuss microinverters or optimizers for shading issues.  \n- **Warranties**: Confirm coverage for equipment, labor, and performance (e.g., 90% output after 25 years).  \n\nBy balancing these factors, you can choose a provider that aligns with your energy needs, budget, and sustainability goals. Always validate credentials and read recent customer testimonials to ensure quality service.",
